# LLM Proxy Three-tier Architecture

## Architecture

```
Handler â†’ Service â†’ Proxy â†’ upstream HTTP
                 â†˜ Converter (pure conversion)
```

| Layer | Responsibility | Rules |
|-------|---------------|-------|
| Service | Endpoint lookup + dispatch + Converter call + message storage | Must NOT contain HTTP request build / SSE read |
| Proxy | HTTP request build + send + SSE read + event merge | Must NOT contain protocol conversion logic; deliver events via callback |
| Converter | Pure DTO format conversion | Stateless, no side effects, no external service dependency |

## Native Protocol Flow (OpenAI Interface â†’ OpenAI Upstream)

```
Client â†’ /api/openai/v1/chat/completions (model=my-alias)
  â†’ APIKeyMiddleware validates Key
  â†’ Service looks up my-alias â†’ ModelEndpoint table (provider=openai)
  â†’ Compatibility handling (e.g. max_tokens â†’ max_completion_tokens)
  â†’ Serialize request, replace model with upstream actual name
  â†’ Proxy builds HTTP request â†’ forward to upstream â†’ SSE read â†’ callback returns chunk
  â†’ Service replaces model name in callback â†’ write to client
  â†’ Async: convert to UnifiedMessage â†’ store via Pool (CheckSum dedup)
```

## Cross-protocol Flow (OpenAI Interface â†’ Anthropic Upstream)

```
Client â†’ /api/openai/v1/chat/completions (model=my-alias)
  â†’ Service looks up my-alias â†’ ModelEndpoint table (provider=anthropic)
  â†’ Converter converts OpenAI request to Anthropic format
  â†’ Proxy sends via Anthropic protocol to upstream
  â†’ Service uses Converter to convert Anthropic events back to OpenAI chunks in callback â†’ write to client
  â†’ Async: Converter converts back to OpenAI format â†’ store via Pool
```

Anthropic interface similarly supports OpenAI upstream (reverse conversion).

## Proxy Streaming Callback Pattern

```go
proxy.ForwardChatCompletionStream(ctx, ep, body, func(chunk *dto.ChatCompletionChunk) error {
    chunk.Model = exposedModel
    fmt.Fprintf(w, "data: %s\n\n", lo.Must1(sonic.Marshal(chunk)))
    return w.Flush()
})
```

## Key Components

- `OpenAIProxy`: `ForwardChatCompletion` / `ForwardChatCompletionStream`
- `AnthropicProxy`: `ForwardCreateMessage` / `ForwardCreateMessageStream` / `ForwardCountTokens`
- `OpenAIProtocolConverter`: Anthropic â†’ OpenAI (`FromAnthropicRequest` / `ToAnthropicResponse` / `ToAnthropicSSEResponse`)
- `AnthropicProtocolConverter`: OpenAI â†’ Anthropic (`FromOpenAIRequest` / `ToOpenAIResponse` / `ToOpenAISSEResponse`)
- `UpstreamEndpoint`: Endpoint info
- `ReplaceModelInBody` / `ReplaceModelInSSEData`: Model replacement utilities

## Async Message Storage

After LLM requests, message storage is submitted to the goroutine pool:
- SHA256 CheckSum-based dedup
- Batch IN query followed by transactional creation of messages/tools/sessions
- Must use `util.CopyContextValues(ctx)` for context in async tasks
